- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with speech-to-speech translation tasks without any transcription or linguistic supervision. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech signals and their translation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a method for training a sequence-to-sequence model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with developing a method for speech-to-speech translation without any transcription or linguistic supervision, which involves the use of AI techniques. 
- cs.SD (Signal Processing) is another possible category as the paper deals with processing speech signals for translation.
